Bailey Says Unwininding Big Banks Would Require Public Money

-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 
2011-10-04T08:59:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/bailey-says-unwininding-big-banks-would-require-public-money.html
The U.K.’s legal framework for bank
resolution “doesn’t have the ability to resolve large banks
without using public money”  Andrew Bailey , director of U.K.
banking supervision at the Financial Services Authority, said in
a speech in Oxford,  England  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
